Higher Education and Training Deputy Minister Mduduzi Manana is concerned at the decline in NSFAS applications for next year.The government urged matriculants to apply for the NSFAS as the closing date approaches.Manana said: The government calls on pupils in matric to apply for funding without delay as applications close at the end of this month. Earlier this month, NSFAS CEO Msulwa Daca said more than 195 668 students had managed to visit the website to register and create a myNSFAS account on the website.Manana said the numbers were disappointing as the scheme supports 480000 finanacially needy students.batandwam@thenewage.co.za